'''Kawaguchi Asama Shrine''' (河口浅間神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Fujikawaguchiko, Minamitsuru District|ja|富士河口湖町|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yamanashi Prefecture|ja|山梨県|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. It is one of the {{ill|Asama shrines|ja|浅間神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and holds historical Rank as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ({{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) {{ill|Ronsha|ja|論社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, with its Rank under the {{ill|Modern type System|ja|近代社格制度|1=Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} being a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. The shrine is part of the World Cultural Heritage designation as a component of "Mount Fuji - Object of Worship and Source of Artistic Inspiration."

== deity ==
The enshrined deity is:
* {{ill|Konohanasakuya-hime|ja|木花咲耶姫命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, referred to as {{ill|Asama Ōkami|ja|浅間大神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} by the shrine. According to the shrine's records, her husband, {{ill|Ninigi|ja|邇邇芸命|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, and her father, {{ill|Ōyamatsumi|ja|大山祇神|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, are also worshipped in the same hall.

== History ==
=== Foundation ===
The shrine was established in 865 (Jōgan 7) to quell the eruption of Mount Fuji that began in 864. The eruption caused extensive damage, which was believed to result from neglect of worship at {{ill|Sengen Shrine|ja|浅間神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Suruga Province|ja|駿河国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Consequently, it was decided to enshrine Asama Ōkami in {{ill|Kai Province|ja|甲斐国|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. The shrine is listed as a {{ill|Myōjin Taisha|ja|名神大社|fr|Myōjin Taisha|zh|名神大社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

The shrine's role as a {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} has been debated, with {{ill|Ichinomiya Asama Shrine (Fuefuki)|lt=Fuefuki City Asama Shrine|ja|浅間神社 (笛吹市)|1=Ichinomiya Asama Shrine (Fuefuki)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in Fuefuki City being another possible site.

=== Development ===
The surrounding area developed as a hub for Mount Fuji worship but declined with the rise of {{ill|Fujikō|ja|富士講|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} pilgrimages in the Edo period. In 1871 (Meiji 4), the shrine was Ranked as a {{ill|District shrine|ja|郷社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, later promoted to a {{ill|Prefectural shrine|ja|県社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} in 1924 (Taishō 13).

== Cultural Properties ==
=== National Historic Site ===
* Part of the "Mount Fuji" Historic Site designation.

=== Important Intangible Folk Cultural Property ===
* {{ill|Chigo no Mai of Kawaguchi|ja|河口の稚児舞|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, designated in 2017.

=== Yamanashi Prefectural Natural Monuments ===
* The "Seven Sacred Cedars" at the shrine are over 1,200 years old.

== Access ==
* Bus: From Kawaguchiko Station (Fujikyuko Line), take a bus bound for Kōfu or Ōishi and get off at "Kawaguchi Post Office." The shrine is a short walk north.

== See Also ==
* {{ill|Asama Shrine|ja|浅間神社|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Ichinomiya Asama Shrine (Fuefuki)|lt=Fuefuki City Asama Shrine|ja|浅間神社 (笛吹市)|1=Ichinomiya Asama Shrine (Fuefuki)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}

